description: What's more refreshing than milk on a hot day? Get a healthy dose of 2% beats to quench your thirst.
Shooby-do-we-bop-bot. Rockabilly Runtime Error brings the kind of sound best listened to on a juke box with a malty in your hand.
Their music might sound cryptic to the average listener, but if you're in the know The Shared Secrets unlock a world of meaning.
Lean back and take the journey with The Honky-Tonk Hardware. They are storytellers, here to share a little love, a little friendship, and a whole lot of heartbreak.
That _That_ has become so popular despite their confusing name is testament to the popularity of her shoegaze-psychadelia sounds. That's all there is to it.
Such fast fingers on the jazz flute have redefined how we understand music, harmony and love itself. You'll love The Asymmetric Keys.
Sittin' on a porch, sippin' on sweet tea, and singin' along with Toothpick Dave.
Give your ears a ride on the retro train. Toot toot, Retromoto is coming around the corner at full jazz.
Don’t get buried in the beats. AVALANCHA cuts new musical terrain right under your feet.
Tabs and Spaces is shaking up the jazz world. Their controversial album _Who Cares, my IDE will handle it_ created a schism in the musical community.
Backslash's iconic song _Character Escape_ captured the hearts of the EDM crowd. Their much anticipated album _Hardcode THIS_ has already presold over a million copies.
Break beat boundaries with us!  The Console Cowboys rope in the newest sounds, ride the latest beats, and wake up your musical animal.
Inspired by science fiction movies, Beebop is like the robot friend your mom wouldn't let you keep. Why bother learning Klingon, when robot speak sounds like this?!

Don't miss this show! Angry Atticus is expected to debut singles from her newest record _FOMO_. Her signature guitar solos mixed with soothing instrumentals are sure to leave you everything but angry.
This Seattle-based artist has tried many different genres but always finds herself coming back to Ukranian Nuclear Fuzz-Grunge.
You're not asleep; the nightmare is real. Revel in it.
Biscuits may haunt you in the morning, but DJ Spooky Biscuits will keep you up at night. Get your night vision ready.
Descafeinado explores the softer side of alternative, blending familiar classical phrases with remixed nature sounds to create something entirely new.
Every time they drop the bass, a database is deleted.
Wintermute turns everything you think you know upside in! Be ready to have your mindblown by this superintelligent musical master.
Leave suburbia in the dust. Suburban Sod will blast your eardrums so you never have to hear the lawnmower again.
Edge Case is most known for their hit _Redmond Rage_ but don't let those slow beats fool you. Ten minutes or less with Edge Case and you will be running for your ear plugs.
Kanban Karate just keeps churning out hits. Once they set their mind on what they need _to do_, they're immediately _in progress_, and then they're _done_!
Freshify your rock with Supermarket Sushi! We keep the beat alive until you're satisfied.
Fans fall in love with the small swings throughout MgC's tracks. Hear the roar of an everyday champion through the billboard hit _Hole in Won_.
The clear headliner. The Accumulators live up to their name, accumulating 14 billboard hits and three gold records. Get to the stage early, this will be a crowded show.

Feature Bug is known for incorporating glitchy electronic sounds with unexpected silences. Their number 1 song _itworks_ contains a one-minute silence in the middle of the track. Unsuspecting listeners may think their headphones are broken, but Feature Bug fans (aka Buggies) know that the silence is exactly what's working.
Be pleasantly surprised by a collection of mash-ups you never thought could work.
Push to Master is as soulful as they are edgy. Their debut album _Never Branch_ stirred up serious controversy in the Indie community.
What's smoother than butter? Buttered Breads.
P Zero unites haunting vocals and room-shaking base. One thing's for sure - you can't ignore P Zero.
Who needs a piano player when you have a player piano? The Convolutional Layers let their instruments do the rocking.
The Map Reducer, best known for her single _Nama-STAR_ is a direct hit at the Northwest yoga community. Kombucha and kale are strictly banned from this show.
The Mean Square Errors are here to show you just how off your estimate is. #MSD

Sure, The Package Managers' first album _Nuget_ had a strong following, but it wasn't until their latest release _NPM_ that they entered the mainstream. Early fans accuse them of selling out, but it's impossible to get hits like _Love Express_ and _Promise You'll Return_ out of your head.
Are you a human? Are you a machine? By the end of her glitch-pop set, The Turing Tester will have you questioning your very existence.
Funny name. Serious music. The Wobble Mops will make you think about your feelings. It's okay to cry.

Poetic lyrics written during long nights at coding events inspired this unlikely trio to enter the music game. Their decade-old debut album -;, still resonates with their software-engineering fanbase.
If music from Stack Trance sounds like an hour-long improvised jam session, that’s because it is. Expect the unexpected! With Stack Trance, you know you won't get the same show twice.

The school of hard knocks molded this crew from the mean streets of Redmond. They spit effortless lyrics of integrated continuity with a linguistic agility rarely seen on the West Coast. There was some fear of a lackluster second album, but The Five Nines Crew continues to drop the mic.
The truth. The whole truth. And nothing but the truth.
Don’t let the name scare you away. Actually, you should probably let the name scare you away…

The founder of educational rap. This old-school band continues to delight audiences with rhymes and styles of a distinctly classic flavor. Their most recent album _Its colon W Q!_ is a direct shot at V.I.M who many feel is a poor, manufactured imitation of The Original V.I.
Zia. Esmina. Nita.  Headed your way.  Just try to zone us out!
The Dixie Flatline puts the I in ROI. He's selfish, smug and the ultimate self-starter. His bandmates do the heavy lifting, which is how he likes it.
V.I.M delivers lyrical rhymes backed by brass instruments.  You might think they sound familiar - expect controversy with The Original V.I sharing the same stage.
Tip of the CaaP may have started from humble roots in rural Montana, but their global fan base can't get enough of hits like _I got nothing to say. Bot, we need to talk._

Heavily inspired by the educational rap movement with the likes of V.I.M and the Original V.I, We As Code integrated elements from genre legends to create something totally new.  We As Code's song _I've got 99 Extensions_ encourages people everywhere to create their own music.

Inspired by the phrase, "first comes the beat, then comes the flow," Beat Flow is known for their ability to incorporate different styles of jazz into one breakout song. Their hit _Type of Scripts_ is  bringing a whole new audience to the improvisational jazz community.
Though sometines tough to get through, Upgrade Path's music will leave you better off.
